  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 41 for SLE 12 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.180-94_150 fixes several issues.\n\nThe following security issues were fixed:\n\n- CVE-2022-0487: A use-after-free vulnerability was found in rtsx_usb_ms_drv_remove() in drivers/memstick/host/rtsx_usb_ms.c (bsc#1194516).\n- CVE-2022-0492: Fixed a privilege escalation related to cgroups v1 release_agent feature, which allowed bypassing namespace isolation unexpectedly (bsc#1195543).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
